50|$|The 2 {{millimeter}} band is {{a portion}} of the EHF (microwave) radio spectrum internationally allocated to amateur radio and <b>amateur</b> <b>satellite</b> use. The amateur radio and <b>amateur</b> <b>satellite</b> band is between 134 GHz and 141 GHz. Amateurs operate on a primary basis between 134 GHz and 136 GHz, and on a secondary basis {{in the rest of the}} band. Also, amateurs must protect the radio astronomy service from harmful interference between 136 GHz and 141 GHz. The ITU's allocations are the same in all three ITU Regions.|$|E
